quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  16,115,"He has only forbidden to you dead animals,{1} blood, the flesh of swine, and that which has been dedicated to other than Allāh. But whoever is forced [by necessity], neither desiring [it] nor transgressing [its limit] - then indeed, Allāh is Forgiving and Merciful.",1:[Those not slaughtered or hunted expressly for food.]
  16,116,"And do not say about what your tongues assert of untruth, "
  16,117,"[It is but] a brief enjoyment, and they will have a painful punishment."
  17,82,"And We send down of the Qur’ān that which is healing and mercy for the believers, but it does not increase the wrongdoers except in loss."
  17,83,"And when We bestow favor upon man [i.e., the disbeliever], he turns away and distances himself; and when evil touches him, he is ever despairing."
  17,84,"Say, "
  18,49,"And the record [of deeds] will be placed [open], and you will see the criminals fearful of that within it, and they will say, "
  18,50,"And [mention] when We said to the angels, "
  18,51,"I did not make them witness to the creation of the heavens and the earth or to the creation of themselves, and I would not have taken the misguiders as assistants."
  19,10,"[Zechariah] said, ",1:[i.e., without illness or defect.]
  19,11,"So he came out to his people from the prayer chamber and signaled to them to exalt [Allāh] in the morning and afternoon."
  19,12,"[Allāh said], "